This is a master course provideed by University of Florida. The main topic of this course is large language model. The course was being seperated into following sections:
1. basic language model like n-gram, word embedding and tokenization techniques
2. Neural architecture for LLMs, language models like RNN and LSTM
3. Attention technique including self-attention and multihead-attention. Intro to transformer structure and transformer based-LLMs
4. Encoder, Encoder-decoder, Decoder only LLMs
5. Traininf and Pre-training for LLMs, training data for LLMs, nference of LLMs including decoding strategies and controllable text generation
6. Fine-tuning LLMs, including fine-tuning, prompt-based tuning, parameter efficient fine-tuning
   Post-training LLMs, including in-context learning, instruction tuning, model alignment
7. Reinforcement Learning in LLMs, including Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO), Direct Preference Optimization (DPO), Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO),  LLMs scaling law and emergent behavior
8. Retrieval-augmented LLMs, Retrieval Augmentation Generation
9. Knowledge-enhanced LLMs, including knowledge extraction, knowledge storage, knowledge editing, knowledge unlearning
10. Reasoning and Planning in LLMs LLM-based agent and multi-agent system LLM harm, debias, detoxification
11. LLM hallucination detection and mitigation Multi-modality LLM, language and vision foundation models
